HEADWORD: Euphotide
<hw>Eu"pho*tide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>e'y^</grk> well + <?/, <?/, light. So called because of its
pleasing combination of white and green.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
rock occurring in the Alps, consisting of saussurite and smaragdite; --
sometimes called <altname>gabbro</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

